Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.83,0:00:06.79,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Closed today for my daughter's culture fair -Kokageya
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.75,0:00:11.39,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,It's raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.39,0:00:13.53,Default,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Radio forecast says it'll let up by afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.61,0:00:16.15,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to a wedding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.80,0:00:23.48,Default,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother always told me to \Ndress appropriately for concerts.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.48,0:00:24.94,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,That's over the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.94,0:00:28.34,Default,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, since today's Sunday, \Nthe dining hall's closed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.34,0:00:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made a lunch for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.63,0:00:31.83,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.78,0:00:34.51,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Good luck, Wakana
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.33,0:00:36.59,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.84,0:00:45.16,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:27.52,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hamada Tetsu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:27.52,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The artwork's done!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:27.52,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It's a true masterpiece!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:27.52,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Gonna crash in the art room, so \Nwake me up when you get to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:30.17,Default,haru,0000,0000,0000,,Tai-kun? It starts at one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.93,0:02:32.50,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:35.63,Default,haru,0000,0000,0000,,Mom wants me to take pictures \Nand send them to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.45,0:02:41.80,Default,shou,0000,0000,0000,,This waterproof case was a smart idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:44.39,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,This is a little embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:48.39,Default,shiho,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so spoiled. You don't \Nknow if anybody else will show.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:51.77,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Well, I guess \NKonatsu might like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.10,0:02:57.03,Default,maki,0000,0000,0000,,Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.79,0:02:58.46,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:02:59.43,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:02.59,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! You've gotta stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:03.53,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Take it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.21,0:03:08.48,Default,mako,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing the White Festival \Neven if you're all alone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:09.55,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.55,0:03:11.09,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it keeps raining?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.17,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,You bet. We'll be in the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:14.93,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,You coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.93,0:03:17.88,Default,mako,0000,0000,0000,,No, someone from the newspaper \Nclub wanted to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.39,0:03:20.42,Default,mako,0000,0000,0000,,I have other plans with my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:24.68,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then ask him to \Nput us on the front page.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:27.71,Default,mako,0000,0000,0000,,Front page? It's the school paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.71,0:03:29.03,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,You're useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.03,0:03:30.15,Default,mako,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.08,0:03:48.67,Default,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Well, do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.67,0:03:50.39,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,I will, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.11,0:04:01.07,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Entry to school grounds \Nprohibited due to construction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.11,0:04:01.07,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Shirohamazaka High School Board
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:08.33,Episode Title,title,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Final Episode \NSunny Days and Crying and Sometimes Singing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:11.26,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect them to go that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.21,0:04:14.77,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news. It's the same at \Nthe bike lot entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:18.48,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,And they have security guards \Nat the parking lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:20.80,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,This would be easy to climb over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:23.60,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,But the people coming to see \Nus won't be able to get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.60,0:04:24.41,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.41,0:04:26.05,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Should we sing here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.46,0:04:28.56,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,I have a raincoat, so I'm fine, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.16,0:04:31.97,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I was a bit naive...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.02,0:04:34.96,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hello? Yeah. You woke up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.97,0:04:33.78,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we at least go in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.78,0:04:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:36.20,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we cut the chain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What? All of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.76,0:04:40.15,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.14,0:04:44.47,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Hamada said the doors \Nto the gym are locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:52.07,Default,sec,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we be on our way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:56.30,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,Those pests.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.25,0:04:58.68,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Taichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.68,0:04:59.55,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.55,0:05:00.92,Default,Sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.92,0:05:02.15,Default,Sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Think you can climb over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:04.28,Default,Sawa,0000,0000,0000,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.78,0:05:13.66,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:15.47,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,It's Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:18.26,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,We forgot some things \Nin our class room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.26,0:05:19.38,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,My gym clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.26,0:05:19.38,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}My recorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.96,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.38,0:05:22.09,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:25.63,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,You're here for that unauthorized \Nculture fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the choir club, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:30.06,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,And sometimes badminton club.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.06,0:05:31.47,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,May we ask who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.02,0:05:34.48,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the chairman of the school board.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:38.38,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,You know you're not \Nallowed here on Sundays.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:40.71,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Please give us permission, \Njust for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.71,0:05:42.23,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,We all prepared for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.58,0:05:44.39,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,You should have gotten my permission
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before you started preparing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.98,0:05:49.07,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Would you have given \Nit to us if we'd asked?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.78,0:05:51.99,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,I would have considered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:55.50,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do it even if \Nyou won't accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.27,0:05:58.36,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,If you do something silly\Nmerely to sing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.36,0:06:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are penalized for it, \Nwon't that affect your futures?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.74,0:06:03.88,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,That's unfair!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.09,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.63,0:06:06.91,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,It's education.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to learn how immature \Nand powerless you youngsters are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.23,0:06:21.73,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your culture fair. \NI will allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:22.90,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Principal Ikezaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.06,0:06:28.53,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,I am the principal of this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:32.37,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,The permission of the chairman is \Nnot needed for a culture fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:34.56,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the chairman does not have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the authority to directly \Npenalize students,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.26,0:06:41.10,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,though he does have \Nthe authority to fire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.16,0:06:44.71,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:47.80,Default,princ,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me for never helping you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,despite being your advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.74,0:06:51.97,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.63,0:06:56.31,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,This situation arose because \Nyour education is subpar!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.71,0:06:58.49,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,You dare speak of education?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:01.71,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,You know nothing about the \Nweaknesses that people have,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.71,0:07:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor the wonderful songs that soothe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.25,0:07:09.04,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,This place might only \Nbe an asset to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.04,0:07:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it means so much more to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:16.49,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you just let \Nthem gather and sing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:18.57,Default,prin,0000,0000,0000,,We're human beings!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.57,0:07:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In times of turmoil, we have to sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:29.84,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:32.47,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dismissing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother coming in tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.54,0:07:37.55,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,Have people stand at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.55,0:07:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bottom of the hill to \Nadvise that it's cancelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.23,0:07:40.85,Default,sec,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.85,0:07:41.95,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Hang o—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.95,0:07:43.84,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,You caused all this extra work
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.84,0:07:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of stuff like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam Vice Principal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.17,0:07:57.49,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,By the time the dismissal \Nprocedure is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:07:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the culture fair will be long finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.44,0:08:05.69,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,The vocal club and the wind \Ninstrument club will be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your main pillars of support \Nfrom the music school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.51,0:08:11.17,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,This is the sheet music for the \Nchorus and the accompaniment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The vocal club and the \Nwind instrument club have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:15.28,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,been practicing it recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:18.01,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right to use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.59,0:08:20.47,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:23.19,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Miyamoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:26.86,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Would you let me conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.33,0:08:30.69,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,this stage you've set up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:36.66,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! We'd love that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.65,0:08:39.14,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,I said enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.14,0:08:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of unlocking \Nthe school gate or the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.57,0:08:45.82,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,I sent the security guards \Nat the parking lot away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.82,0:08:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will guide the guests \Ninside from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.98,0:08:50.27,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,What about the stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.45,0:08:55.68,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,The rain has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:04.51,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,This is so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.51,0:09:06.61,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like anyone will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:08.90,Default,wate,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, looks like I'm early.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.47,0:09:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.61,0:09:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the White Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.82,0:09:14.98,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Watermelon, watermelon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.98,0:09:15.95,Default,saw,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.96,0:09:18.96,Default,boy,0000,0000,0000,,We're not the first ones here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.47,0:09:21.41,Default,boy,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.28,0:09:25.66,Default,boy,0000,0000,0000,,You better sing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:28.35,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,He's like a mini Konatsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.35,0:09:29.33,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.10,0:09:37.50,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,You're way too early!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:40.92,Default,ass,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous. We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.59,0:09:50.38,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry along, the other students \Nare setting up inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:51.10,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.10,0:09:51.82,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.25,0:09:53.08,Default,all,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:04.71,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Ueno-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:07.76,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd come!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.70,0:10:11.87,Default,ueno,0000,0000,0000,,Hirohata-san asked the vice principal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.87,0:10:13.96,Default,hir,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't make up weird stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:16.38,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Hirohata-san, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.04,0:10:20.74,Default,hiro,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the vocal club needed \Na goal to work toward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:25.93,text,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}General Building | Music Building
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:25.93,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this is stage left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:28.28,Default,uen,0000,0000,0000,,Then the piano would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.28,0:10:30.59,Default,kura,0000,0000,0000,,And the orchestra pit is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.59,0:10:31.44,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:34.23,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,The quality is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:36.07,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,That's nice. Could you help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:39.74,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,We can rehearse once at most, if that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:43.06,Default,hiro,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it like you practiced, \Nand we'll adjust on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.06,0:10:43.97,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.74,0:10:48.37,text,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}White Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:48.37,Default,girls,0000,0000,0000,,Please enter here for \Nthe White Festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.94,0:10:50.83,Default,girl,0000,0000,0000,,The White Festival is this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness it stopped raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.12,0:10:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.25,0:11:01.59,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,No weird improv during \Nthe real performance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.59,0:11:03.23,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.23,0:11:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put a lot of thought into it \Nso it won't ruin the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.05,0:11:08.61,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm worried about!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:24.48,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Country of \NSound, Shirohama Saga.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:29.39,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Our tale begins as Konacchine \Nsets out on her journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.39,0:11:30.27,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:34.04,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot remain in this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:35.09,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.51,0:11:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where will you go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.39,0:11:40.42,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,To the faraway land of Amano Iward.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:44.51,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit, ribbit! \NI'm the frog, Taiichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.51,0:11:48.45,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm the prince of frogs, Wienaria!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:47.95,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:49.43,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Damn him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.76,0:11:56.36,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,We overcame many difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.93,0:11:59.19,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,But now we're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.34,0:12:03.09,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Though we lost much along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.09,0:12:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Family and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.14,0:12:06.62,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Dreams and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:09.33,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Even our beloved homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.19,0:12:12.91,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we're alone in a world \Nshrouded in darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.91,0:12:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on a path that can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:15.78,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Fear not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of singing will show us the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:21.16,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Then let us sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that we may be \Neach other's humble guides.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.77,0:12:26.93,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it won't bring about a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.93,0:12:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for that single moment of rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:32.41,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,We'll pour our feelings \Ninto this song...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:35.98,Default,all,0000,0000,0000,,And start walking again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:54.52,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Under the blue sky
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.91,0:13:03.90,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}we spread our arms wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:11.06,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doubt and pain are \Nproof that we had hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.40,0:13:17.32,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll go at our own pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:26.02,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll always have faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:36.62,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A passing shower will \Neventually come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:43.60,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even filled with tears, \Nour hearts can be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.60,0:13:51.01,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because, look, someone will be \Nthere to pat our backs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.42,0:13:57.87,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This melody will bring out the light
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.87,0:14:05.15,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and reflect tomorrow in \Nthese sparkling eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.79,0:14:08.37,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Filled with dreams, \Nour hearts will always be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:15.88,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because, look, someone will be \Nthere to laugh with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:22.67,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This melody beckons the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:29.11,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the path is a winding one, \Neverything will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.11,0:14:42.52,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We can set out with \Nsmiles on our faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.51,0:15:37.55,Default,Wien,0000,0000,0000,,Jan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.13,0:15:51.75,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Look at him, with his happy grin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.75,0:15:53.39,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Fall, fall, fall, fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.39,0:15:54.75,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,He can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.75,0:15:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was accepted based \Non his recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:00.58,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After graduation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:09.11,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Abroad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:10.66,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are equestrian \Nschools abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.27,0:16:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I go, there's a chance \NI could still be a jockey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:17.25,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:18.28,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:20.46,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,It will be really difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.46,0:16:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if I come back from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.07,0:16:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might be able to be a \Njockey here in Japan, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.53,0:16:25.38,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.82,0:16:27.12,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,How's your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.12,0:16:28.34,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.71,0:16:30.84,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,That school will have exams, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.55,0:16:34.08,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I want to go over \Nthere as soon as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and start learning the language first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.57,0:16:38.47,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,When's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.82,0:16:40.83,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.21,0:16:43.40,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,But what about school?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.01,0:16:45.87,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,I considered dropping out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I talked to our teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.37,0:16:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they said they'd \Nstill let me graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.10,0:16:51.80,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they don't want to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.80,0:16:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,graduates because of what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.83,0:16:55.70,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,So it's a done deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:16:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.79,0:17:00.00,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:03.16,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,For how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.59,0:17:07.09,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Until I'm satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.06,0:17:11.29,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:13.06,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come back crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.16,0:17:15.93,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.99,0:17:18.30,Default,wak,0000,0000,0000,,Are you taking Sabure?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:19.58,Default,sawa,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.48,0:17:26.10,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A fresh wind races through the grass and leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Make sure you spend time with her now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:23.03,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Where abroad? Mongolia?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.10,0:17:34.17,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The view is clear, as far as the eye can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.17,0:17:42.01,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And now, a graceful light is flooding,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:50.60,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}softly illuminating everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:56.35,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if you can't see the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.35,0:17:59.79,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because of the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:04.65,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the future you're dreaming of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:07.15,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}is still right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.15,0:18:11.57,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's sing every day
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:15.63,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with all our hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.63,0:18:19.97,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}our song echoing to the skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.97,0:18:22.78,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:27.26,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And if it should ever
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:31.12,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}reach you again somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:35.42,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want you to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:43.31,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the days we spent with sparkling eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:37.40,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Sakai-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.45,0:18:39.91,text,book,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Melody of the Heart
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:41.39,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,This is your sheet music, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:43.65,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:51.47,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The days we spent with beaming smiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.65,0:18:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the competition we signed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.74,0:18:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each other's music and exchanged it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.47,0:18:53.65,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever I was with Mahiru,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.65,0:18:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt like I had talent as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:19:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wasn't able to walk the same
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.96,0:19:03.29,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,musical path that she walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was jealous and ashamed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.36,0:19:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I still couldn't throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.58,0:19:12.50,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I think my mother would tell you not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.43,0:19:17.01,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I found this when I was sorting \Nthrough her belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.48,0:19:21.45,text,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Melody of the Heart \NTakakura Naoko
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.59,0:19:20.59,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,My mother always seemed to \Nhave fun singing this song.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.44,0:19:24.75,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,Mahiru was always having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.75,0:19:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were times when that \Nmade me jealous and angry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.85,0:19:30.01,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I think I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.63,0:19:34.13,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,That feeling that things \Ncome to her so naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.98,0:19:38.94,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I want to dedicate myself \Nto studying music.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.48,0:19:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might not be able \Nto make it this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.68,0:19:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I want to go to that \Nkind of university.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:45.40,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,Could I talk with you about those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.40,0:19:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,kinds of topics \Neven after I graduate?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.45,0:19:53.04,Default,vice,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am{\i0} a music teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.28,0:20:05.21,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to hear the voice \Nof the white beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.21,0:20:10.35,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so let's climb that winding slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:10.33,Default,banner,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}2nd Shirohamazaka High School
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:10.33,Default,banner,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Graduation Ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.65,0:20:16.90,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The friendships we forge during \Nthese brilliant days and moments,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:21.75,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}create a harmony that stretches across eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:24.30,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Allegro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.30,0:20:25.81,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Vivace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.81,0:20:27.28,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:28.76,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.47,0:20:34.29,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.73,0:20:36.29,Default,shi,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'm taking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.78,0:20:38.26,Default,shi,0000,0000,0000,,One plus one is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.26,0:20:39.51,Default,all,0000,0000,0000,,Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:42.22,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's this two business?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.22,0:20:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me these things ahead of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.46,0:20:47.00,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Please take another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.00,0:20:49.27,Default,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it's a great shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.88,0:20:52.12,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka, don't you have \Nanything special to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:53.60,Default,tai,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, shrimp!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.60,0:20:55.11,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, he's embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.35,0:20:56.73,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sawa, I'll come visit you sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:58.11,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.31,0:21:01.34,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the Shirohamazaka \NHigh School's Choir
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.34,0:21:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Sometimes Badminton Club \Nwill sing one last song!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.94,0:21:07.45,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.45,0:21:12.59,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A new wind blows,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.73,0:21:20.46,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}laughing, crying, and trying to sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:25.83,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Open your closed heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.83,0:21:32.98,Default,song,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hum the harmony of the sea breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.13,0:22:09.26,Default,wien,0000,0000,0000,,Jan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.07,0:22:11.85,Default,jan,0000,0000,0000,,Matsuhiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.50,0:22:21.74,Default,girl,0000,0000,0000,,Miyamoto-san, have you \Npicked a club yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.74,0:22:23.56,Default,kona,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.56,0:22:25.99,Default,girl,0000,0000,0000,,How about this? Join us!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.67,0:23:10.97,Default,rad,0000,0000,0000,,August will see quite a \Nfew nice summer days,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.97,0:23:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ushering in the summer holiday \Natmosphere to the whole country.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.40,0:23:18.01,Default,rad,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the forecast \Nfor the Kanto region.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.89,0:23:30.26,Default,waka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.26,0:23:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
